1
00:02:13,260 --> 00:02:15,940
Run for Young

2
00:02:16,660 --> 00:02:18,100
Fate is decided by destiny.

3
00:02:18,420 --> 00:02:19,740
Happiness is your own.

4
00:02:20,180 --> 00:02:21,940
Want to learn if he or she is your fate?

5
00:02:22,500 --> 00:02:23,540
Send your name

6
00:02:23,540 --> 00:02:25,020
and his or her name,

7
00:02:25,140 --> 00:02:29,740
for example, Guo Jing and Huang Rong, to 10082588

8
00:02:29,780 --> 00:02:31,300
to find out if you are

9
00:02:31,300 --> 00:02:32,380
meant to be together.

10
00:02:48,620 --> 00:02:49,579
Where were you?

11
00:02:51,780 --> 00:02:52,420
What's the fuss?

12
00:03:08,660 --> 00:03:10,380
Give up right now,

13
00:03:10,380 --> 00:03:11,900
even a rotten wood won't break.

14
00:03:12,140 --> 00:03:13,980
Fate is already decided,

15
00:03:15,780 --> 00:03:16,980
and it can't be forced.

16
00:03:17,540 --> 00:03:19,260
If I don't give up,

17
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:20,860
it won't make a difference.

18
00:03:21,220 --> 00:03:24,420
Like the peacock flying southeast.

19
00:03:34,020 --> 00:03:35,300
There's no difference.

20
00:03:38,300 --> 00:03:39,580
You and Chen Xi have my blessing.

21
00:03:41,100 --> 00:03:43,060
Would you still like to be my friend?

22
00:03:43,740 --> 00:03:46,580
I mean just normal friends.

23
00:03:49,420 --> 00:03:50,260
That's it.

24
00:04:12,100 --> 00:04:16,060
Episode 3 About to Fall in Love

25
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:29,340
I haven't said happy birthday to you yet.

26
00:04:29,340 --> 00:04:30,660
I'm very happy today!

27
00:04:30,660 --> 00:04:31,620
Why are you happy?

28
00:04:31,660 --> 00:04:33,180
You gave me the best birthday present.

29
00:04:34,220 --> 00:04:35,340
It's nothing really.

30
00:04:35,420 --> 00:04:37,100
My old man has loads of pork livers.

31
00:04:38,900 --> 00:04:39,660
Oh right,

32
00:04:39,660 --> 00:04:41,340
does he have a girlfriend?

33
00:04:41,340 --> 00:04:42,060
Who?

34
00:04:42,460 --> 00:04:43,080
That's Liu...

35
00:04:43,420 --> 00:04:44,060
My big brother.

36
00:04:45,340 --> 00:04:46,660
He used to have a girlfriend.

37
00:04:47,620 --> 00:04:49,060
Not sure how he's coping with that.

38
00:04:49,100 --> 00:04:50,060
Really?

39
00:04:50,100 --> 00:04:51,540
Has he ever talked to you about it?

40
00:04:51,860 --> 00:04:53,300
He never speaks to us about that.

41
00:04:56,900 --> 00:04:57,619
Oh right,

42
00:04:58,100 --> 00:05:00,059
you still haven't told me about the pork liver.

43
00:05:00,460 --> 00:05:01,260
Delicious!

44
00:05:42,380 --> 00:05:49,460
In the ocean of suffering, roll waves of love and hate

45
00:05:50,220 --> 00:05:58,260
In this world, it's hard to escape your fate

46
00:06:00,220 --> 00:06:08,020
Being in love but not being able to be together

47
00:06:08,540 --> 00:06:10,780
Maybe I should

48
00:06:33,340 --> 00:06:34,140
Qin.

49
00:06:36,660 --> 00:06:37,540
My classmate Anran.

50
00:06:38,180 --> 00:06:39,460
She's been wondering about you.

51
00:06:51,780 --> 00:06:53,300
She looks like a good student.

52
00:06:53,460 --> 00:06:54,820
Don't bring her here.

53
00:06:56,860 --> 00:06:58,260
Qin, you don't know her.

54
00:06:58,260 --> 00:06:59,540
She's cool.

55
00:07:01,940 --> 00:07:02,740
Get her away.

56
00:07:17,780 --> 00:07:19,980
Qin's always been

57
00:07:21,020 --> 00:07:22,180
one of those cool kids.

58
00:07:23,540 --> 00:07:24,260
Don't worry.

59
00:07:24,260 --> 00:07:25,460
After you get along, you'll see

60
00:07:25,460 --> 00:07:26,380
he's really a nice guy.

61
00:07:28,380 --> 00:07:30,380
It's too late now.

62
00:07:30,380 --> 00:07:31,620
We'll come again.

63
00:07:59,380 --> 00:08:01,020
It's the same song!

64
00:08:14,940 --> 00:08:18,140
I'm afraid I'm falling in love!

65
00:08:18,620 --> 00:08:22,460
I'm afraid I'm falling in love!

66
00:08:22,740 --> 00:08:27,180
I'm afraid I'm falling in love!

67
00:08:44,020 --> 00:08:45,580
I'll be honest with you.

68
00:08:46,340 --> 00:08:48,500
The school is only asking you to do this as a formality.

69
00:08:49,420 --> 00:08:50,780
But for us,

70
00:08:51,340 --> 00:08:52,740
since we're already running,

71
00:08:52,860 --> 00:08:53,940
we must give it our best!

72
00:08:55,180 --> 00:08:55,900
Understand?

73
00:08:56,380 --> 00:08:57,000
Yes, sir!

74
00:09:09,820 --> 00:09:10,740
Slow down!

75
00:09:23,019 --> 00:09:25,320
I'll have a pea paste noodle. Extra spicy.

76
00:09:25,320 --> 00:09:25,940
Sure.

77
00:09:25,940 --> 00:09:27,580
I'll have a Chongqing noodle.

78
00:09:27,780 --> 00:09:29,460
I'll have a pea paste noodle with an egg.

79
00:09:32,700 --> 00:09:33,300
You're back.

80
00:09:33,700 --> 00:09:34,580
What did you get?

81
00:09:34,820 --> 00:09:35,580
Just the usual.

82
00:09:35,660 --> 00:09:36,820
I'll have a noodle.

83
00:09:36,860 --> 00:09:37,580
Coming.

84
00:09:37,580 --> 00:09:38,260
Take a seat.

85
00:09:46,660 --> 00:09:47,620
Can't stir your noodles?

86
00:09:49,620 --> 00:09:50,220
I'll help.

87
00:09:58,380 --> 00:09:58,980
Thanks, Doggo.

88
00:10:01,140 --> 00:10:02,100
Cut it.

89
00:10:02,300 --> 00:10:03,540
Still calling me Doggo?

90
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:08,020
How should she call you, if not Doggo?

91
00:10:08,260 --> 00:10:09,340
Junjun?

92
00:10:09,380 --> 00:10:11,060
She can call me whatever she likes.

93
00:10:11,780 --> 00:10:12,740
Then go for it.

94
00:10:14,220 --> 00:10:14,820
It's alright.

95
00:10:15,220 --> 00:10:15,820
I'll do it.

96
00:10:25,300 --> 00:10:26,260
It's alright. Just eat.

97
00:10:39,260 --> 00:10:40,540
Don't know how to eat noodles?

98
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:42,060
You're body is so tense.

99
00:10:43,060 --> 00:10:44,220
Turn around. I'll teach you.

100
00:10:48,220 --> 00:10:49,700
The right way to eat noodles.

101
00:10:50,540 --> 00:10:51,700
Step on the bench.

102
00:10:53,180 --> 00:10:54,140
Shoes off?

103
00:10:54,180 --> 00:10:55,020
Whatever.

104
00:10:57,020 --> 00:10:58,580
Pull your pants up.

105
00:10:58,660 --> 00:10:59,660
Put your arm on it.

106
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:00,300
Tap your foot.

107
00:11:01,180 --> 00:11:02,500
Hold your bowl, eat as you tap.

108
00:11:03,780 --> 00:11:04,460
Like me.

109
00:11:12,780 --> 00:11:13,700
Tastes better this way?

110
00:11:16,140 --> 00:11:16,860
I suppose so.

111
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:21,860
You look so awkward!

112
00:11:21,860 --> 00:11:24,140
You can't even eat your noodles right! I'm done!

113
00:11:27,260 --> 00:11:27,900
I'll feed you.

114
00:11:28,260 --> 00:11:29,460
There's no way I'll eat it.

115
00:11:30,820 --> 00:11:31,540
Stop it!

116
00:11:31,540 --> 00:11:32,300
Come on.

117
00:11:32,300 --> 00:11:33,060
You're so annoying!

118
00:11:33,060 --> 00:11:34,100
Doggo, Teaty is hitting me!

119
00:11:41,180 --> 00:11:42,140
Anran, come on.

120
00:11:46,220 --> 00:11:46,820
Let's go.

121
00:11:55,100 --> 00:11:56,180
So?

122
00:11:56,540 --> 00:11:58,020
I saw him.

123
00:11:58,220 --> 00:11:58,820
I know.

124
00:11:59,220 --> 00:12:00,540
I mean how is he?

125
00:12:00,660 --> 00:12:01,740
Same as you imagined?

126
00:12:03,900 --> 00:12:05,980
I think those people are quite complicated.

127
00:12:06,060 --> 00:12:07,220
I'm worried about you.

128
00:12:07,300 --> 00:12:09,140
Since when did I need others to worry about me?

129
00:12:10,260 --> 00:12:12,060
Do you really know what you want?

130
00:12:51,460 --> 00:12:52,740
Give me a second. Be right back.

131
00:13:07,860 --> 00:13:09,180
Watch the puddle.

132
00:13:09,460 --> 00:13:10,180
You again!

133
00:13:10,940 --> 00:13:12,620
You always have company lately.

134
00:13:13,740 --> 00:13:15,700
Wasn't ever alone before.

135
00:13:16,660 --> 00:13:17,620
That's different.

136
00:13:17,620 --> 00:13:18,300
Enough.

137
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:19,260
Enjoy yourself.

138
00:13:21,420 --> 00:13:22,040
Qin.

139
00:13:24,340 --> 00:13:25,300
I'm here.

140
00:13:25,420 --> 00:13:26,020
Which one?

141
00:13:26,540 --> 00:13:27,700
I'm going pick one.

142
00:13:28,220 --> 00:13:29,100
Yagami.

143
00:13:29,100 --> 00:13:29,780
Random choice.

144
00:13:29,780 --> 00:13:30,580
I'll bust you!

145
00:13:49,300 --> 00:13:50,260
It's her again.

146
00:13:54,660 --> 00:13:55,540
Qin.

147
00:13:56,100 --> 00:13:58,220
Are you really annoyed with girls?

148
00:13:58,460 --> 00:13:59,500
It's not like that.

149
00:13:59,900 --> 00:14:01,300
She looks like a good student.

150
00:14:01,620 --> 00:14:03,780
Teachers told us not to bother good students.

151
00:14:04,260 --> 00:14:06,180
She's a new transfer.

152
00:14:06,180 --> 00:14:07,780
She probably never met people like us.

153
00:14:08,980 --> 00:14:10,580
She keeps bothering me. It's so annoying.

154
00:14:10,980 --> 00:14:12,260
Have you taken a liking to her?

155
00:14:13,340 --> 00:14:14,100
Nonsense!

156
00:14:14,300 --> 00:14:15,300
Can I join you?

157
00:14:15,340 --> 00:14:16,300
- Sure. - No.

158
00:14:20,220 --> 00:14:21,420
There are many bad guys here.

159
00:14:22,260 --> 00:14:23,340
Just leave.

160
00:14:25,500 --> 00:14:26,460
I'm not a good student.

161
00:14:27,100 --> 00:14:28,060
You're not a bad guy.

162
00:14:30,540 --> 00:14:31,140
Come.

163
00:14:31,620 --> 00:14:32,740
I'll make a toast.

164
00:14:33,060 --> 00:14:33,900
You drink?

165
00:14:34,180 --> 00:14:35,380
I don't drink with girls.

166
00:14:38,820 --> 00:14:39,440
Listen to me.

167
00:14:39,980 --> 00:14:40,700
Have...

168
00:14:41,020 --> 00:14:41,980
Have green tea along.

169
00:14:43,220 --> 00:14:44,100
Bottoms up.

170
00:14:44,460 --> 00:14:45,300
Forget it.

171
00:14:45,540 --> 00:14:46,540
Forget about alcohol.

172
00:14:46,540 --> 00:14:47,860
Qin, not this time.

173
00:14:48,020 --> 00:14:48,780
Get to the arcade.

174
00:14:49,460 --> 00:14:50,080
Get to...

175
00:14:54,900 --> 00:14:55,540
Doggo.

176
00:14:57,180 --> 00:14:58,980
This place is for guys.

177
00:14:59,100 --> 00:15:00,580
Don't bring girls here anymore.

178
00:15:02,940 --> 00:15:04,220
I wanted to come.

179
00:15:07,140 --> 00:15:09,620
Alright, sit down.

180
00:15:11,860 --> 00:15:13,260
It's not that Qin doesn't like you.

181
00:15:13,300 --> 00:15:15,060
He just doesn't know you yet.

182
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:16,340
It just takes time.

183
00:15:20,820 --> 00:15:22,260
Qin grills them himself?

184
00:15:22,940 --> 00:15:23,540
Yeah.

185
00:15:23,900 --> 00:15:24,820
He owns this place.

186
00:15:25,260 --> 00:15:26,580
Isn't he your big brother?

187
00:15:26,780 --> 00:15:27,700
Why is he running this?

188
00:15:33,740 --> 00:15:35,420
That's a long story.

189
00:15:37,540 --> 00:15:39,540
Qin didn't make the professional basketball team.

190
00:15:40,300 --> 00:15:41,420
His father was seriously ill.

191
00:15:42,580 --> 00:15:45,660
He was forced to make a living at an early age.

192
00:15:49,020 --> 00:15:50,020
So that's the case.

193
00:15:51,380 --> 00:15:52,140
What?

194
00:15:53,340 --> 00:15:54,140
Nothing.

195
00:15:54,740 --> 00:15:56,460
I just think he's been through a lot.

196
00:16:03,380 --> 00:16:04,580
Which dog is this?

197
00:16:05,060 --> 00:16:06,140
All alone here.

198
00:16:07,820 --> 00:16:10,060
I was wondering why this place stinks.

199
00:16:10,420 --> 00:16:12,300
You got business? Get lost.

200
00:16:14,220 --> 00:16:15,780
Her family must be rich.

201
00:16:16,620 --> 00:16:17,500
None of your business.

202
00:16:18,700 --> 00:16:21,900
A rich girl can only come to
a skewers stall with a poor guy like you.

203
00:16:22,020 --> 00:16:22,780
What a shame.

204
00:16:23,460 --> 00:16:24,420
Trying to play a bully?

205
00:16:27,220 --> 00:16:28,500
So what if he's poor at this age?

206
00:16:29,140 --> 00:16:30,420
That only says they're not

207
00:16:30,420 --> 00:16:31,580
wasting their parents' money.

208
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:33,700
But look at you.

209
00:16:33,780 --> 00:16:34,900
You don't look that young,

210
00:16:34,900 --> 00:16:36,580
and you're still wasting your life.

211
00:16:37,220 --> 00:16:39,140
There's probably no girl who likes you.

212
00:16:44,380 --> 00:16:46,220
So what if you take a girl to a skewers stall?

213
00:16:46,620 --> 00:16:47,820
So what if you're poor?

214
00:16:48,580 --> 00:16:49,780
I don't care.

215
00:17:04,020 --> 00:17:05,140
Get lost.

216
00:17:23,140 --> 00:17:23,820
Thanks, Qin.

217
00:17:24,340 --> 00:17:25,380
Try these.

218
00:17:25,660 --> 00:17:26,540
They're delicious.

219
00:18:21,380 --> 00:18:23,100
I took Anran out yesterday.

220
00:18:23,140 --> 00:18:24,180
We also saw Qin.

221
00:18:24,220 --> 00:18:26,220
She can't help but idolize me.

222
00:18:26,220 --> 00:18:27,220
Look at Doggo.

223
00:18:27,540 --> 00:18:28,300
Living the life!

224
00:18:28,700 --> 00:18:29,900
Reflect on that, Teaty.

225
00:18:29,900 --> 00:18:30,540
Mouthy,

226
00:18:30,580 --> 00:18:31,900
Why do you think her and Ma Tian

227
00:18:31,980 --> 00:18:33,380
transferred her at 12th grade?

228
00:18:33,740 --> 00:18:34,420
This is funny.

229
00:18:34,900 --> 00:18:37,420
They must be up to something.

230
00:18:41,180 --> 00:18:41,860
Aunty,

231
00:18:43,700 --> 00:18:44,620
The butcher sent me.

232
00:18:46,380 --> 00:18:47,700
Thank your dad for me.

233
00:18:47,700 --> 00:18:48,580
You're welcome.

234
00:18:48,660 --> 00:18:49,420
Bye, Aunty.

235
00:18:49,420 --> 00:18:50,020
Bye.

236
00:18:53,300 --> 00:18:55,100
Doggo, you're delivering the pork,

237
00:18:55,140 --> 00:18:56,540
but I didn't see them pay you.

238
00:18:57,300 --> 00:18:58,060
The butcher said,

239
00:18:58,100 --> 00:18:59,820
these are all monthly VIP subscribers.

240
00:18:59,820 --> 00:19:00,700
They've already paid.

241
00:19:01,740 --> 00:19:02,820
How much is the plan?

242
00:19:03,580 --> 00:19:05,060
I'll ask my dad to subscribe.

243
00:19:05,060 --> 00:19:06,460
Ask him yourself.

244
00:19:06,460 --> 00:19:07,820
Apart from Hercules Jiao,

245
00:19:07,900 --> 00:19:09,260
who else dares speak to your dad?

246
00:19:09,460 --> 00:19:10,180
He looks vicious.

247
00:19:10,180 --> 00:19:11,220
He's mad every day.

248
00:19:23,540 --> 00:19:24,860
We have some pork

249
00:19:24,980 --> 00:19:26,340
for dinner again.

250
00:19:26,340 --> 00:19:27,900
Who gave it to us?

251
00:19:29,740 --> 00:19:32,220
Must be a living Buddha sent by

252
00:19:32,900 --> 00:19:33,940
your dad from heaven.

253
00:19:33,980 --> 00:19:36,620
What does the living Buddha look like?

254
00:19:36,700 --> 00:19:40,420
He has a benign look.

255
00:19:40,580 --> 00:19:42,420
Gentle and kind.

256
00:19:42,620 --> 00:19:44,780
I'll bomb you son of a turtle.

257
00:19:46,180 --> 00:19:47,020
Son of a turtle.

258
00:19:47,380 --> 00:19:49,140
Did you make every delivery? Miss any?

259
00:19:49,260 --> 00:19:50,140
Yep.

260
00:19:50,860 --> 00:19:52,380
I'll beat you up, believe it?

261
00:19:53,660 --> 00:19:55,060
We didn't miss any delivery.

262
00:19:55,100 --> 00:19:56,260
Don't worry, uncle.

263
00:19:57,260 --> 00:19:58,300
Jiaojiao is the lovely one.

264
00:19:58,300 --> 00:19:58,900
Come.

265
00:19:58,980 --> 00:20:00,060
Here. Get me some noodles.

266
00:20:00,300 --> 00:20:00,920
Sure.

267
00:20:01,660 --> 00:20:02,340
Your turn.

268
00:20:03,340 --> 00:20:05,220
Dad, two noodles.

269
00:20:05,420 --> 00:20:06,060
How about this?

270
00:20:06,400 --> 00:20:07,020
Go on.

271
00:20:07,300 --> 00:20:07,900
Two bowls.

272
00:20:08,060 --> 00:20:09,100
Thanks, dad.

273
00:20:16,380 --> 00:20:17,340
Uncle.

274
00:20:17,420 --> 00:20:18,300
Thanks.

275
00:20:19,980 --> 00:20:20,580
Doggo

276
00:20:22,740 --> 00:20:23,340
Jiaojiao,

277
00:20:23,860 --> 00:20:25,940
I thought I only gave you money for one.

278
00:20:26,540 --> 00:20:28,220
You paid for two.

279
00:20:28,340 --> 00:20:29,620
Really?

280
00:20:29,780 --> 00:20:30,380
Yeah.

281
00:20:30,420 --> 00:20:32,100
He paid for four bowls.

282
00:20:32,100 --> 00:20:33,180
Where are mine and Teaty's?

283
00:20:33,180 --> 00:20:34,500
Yeah, why don't we get some?

284
00:20:35,060 --> 00:20:37,020
Jiaojiao cares for her family.

285
00:20:37,380 --> 00:20:37,980
Jiaojiao,

286
00:20:38,860 --> 00:20:39,820
be my daughter-in-law.

287
00:20:39,900 --> 00:20:40,500
Alright?

288
00:20:46,380 --> 00:20:47,460
What's up?

289
00:20:48,140 --> 00:20:50,500
You think you son of a turtle deserve Jiaojiao?

290
00:20:50,620 --> 00:20:52,260
Stop making a scene.

291
00:20:52,260 --> 00:20:53,420
I don't deserve her.

292
00:20:53,420 --> 00:20:54,820
My dad is a turtle.

293
00:20:54,820 --> 00:20:55,780
I'm a son of a turtle.

294
00:20:55,940 --> 00:20:57,780
Turtles don't deserve humans.

295
00:20:58,780 --> 00:21:00,060
Makes sense.

296
00:21:05,180 --> 00:21:06,260
Dad!

297
00:21:08,900 --> 00:21:09,500
Jiaojiao.

298
00:21:11,900 --> 00:21:13,820
She took money for one bowl,

299
00:21:13,820 --> 00:21:14,940
but brought out two bowls.

300
00:21:15,660 --> 00:21:17,620
Can't she count?

301
00:21:17,620 --> 00:21:19,220
She's in the 12th grade.

302
00:21:19,500 --> 00:21:20,380
That's trouble!

303
00:21:20,900 --> 00:21:21,700
Her?

304
00:21:22,180 --> 00:21:23,540
She's an expert on calculations.

305
00:21:23,540 --> 00:21:24,500
Why can't I see it?

306
00:21:25,180 --> 00:21:26,060
What do you know?

307
00:21:26,700 --> 00:21:28,300
That extra one is called love.

308
00:21:29,380 --> 00:21:30,460
Nonsense.

309
00:21:30,620 --> 00:21:31,900
They two

310
00:21:32,020 --> 00:21:33,660
only have brotherhood.

311
00:21:33,860 --> 00:21:35,220
That's normal.

312
00:21:35,220 --> 00:21:36,340
She's still a child.

313
00:21:36,540 --> 00:21:38,460
She can't tell what's love yet.

314
00:21:40,660 --> 00:21:42,180
But someday,

315
00:21:42,260 --> 00:21:43,540
she'll meet a man

316
00:21:44,220 --> 00:21:47,340
who will make her heart beat so fast that it's going to

317
00:21:47,380 --> 00:21:48,500
jump out of her body.

318
00:21:49,220 --> 00:21:50,260
That's when she'll get it.

319
00:21:51,660 --> 00:21:53,540
I see. It's you entering the mating season.

320
00:21:53,780 --> 00:21:54,400
Hey!

321
00:22:04,300 --> 00:22:05,020
What's up?

322
00:22:07,700 --> 00:22:09,940
Those three said they're having a serious discussion.

323
00:22:12,420 --> 00:22:13,380
What are they up to?

324
00:22:13,820 --> 00:22:16,100
Our city is getting better and better.

325
00:22:16,460 --> 00:22:17,500
Doggo.

326
00:22:17,780 --> 00:22:18,820
The sun is scorching here.

327
00:22:19,420 --> 00:22:21,060
Just cut to the chase.

328
00:22:21,380 --> 00:22:22,780
We've been standing here so long.

329
00:22:26,260 --> 00:22:27,260
You know me.

330
00:22:29,420 --> 00:22:30,620
I'm saying, if.

331
00:22:31,260 --> 00:22:31,860
I mean if.

332
00:22:32,180 --> 00:22:33,580
If you like a girl,

333
00:22:34,820 --> 00:22:35,540
what would you do?

334
00:22:37,020 --> 00:22:37,860
So

335
00:22:38,380 --> 00:22:39,900
you have feelings for a girl,

336
00:22:39,900 --> 00:22:41,940
and you want to tell her, right?

337
00:22:43,660 --> 00:22:45,060
How should I do it?

338
00:22:45,900 --> 00:22:47,380
Wants to express feelings.

339
00:22:48,140 --> 00:22:49,380
Who wants to express?

340
00:22:49,500 --> 00:22:50,260
To whom?

341
00:22:53,260 --> 00:22:55,020
Read his lips.

342
00:22:57,180 --> 00:22:58,220
Doggo is going to.

343
00:22:58,700 --> 00:23:00,100
You can tell that?

344
00:23:00,900 --> 00:23:02,300
There's nothing you can't do.

345
00:23:02,340 --> 00:23:03,100
Probably.

346
00:23:03,100 --> 00:23:03,820
I can do it too.

347
00:23:06,900 --> 00:23:07,520
Is that so?

348
00:23:08,260 --> 00:23:09,180
Then let's try it.

349
00:23:10,380 --> 00:23:10,980
Go for it.

350
00:23:23,780 --> 00:23:25,380
Anran is pretty.

351
00:23:26,660 --> 00:23:29,580
Yeah, you all think she's pretty.

352
00:23:29,580 --> 00:23:31,020
Everything of her is pretty.

353
00:23:31,060 --> 00:23:32,900
So pretty that Doggo wants to confess to her.

354
00:23:42,340 --> 00:23:43,620
Someone wants the same with you.

355
00:23:44,020 --> 00:23:44,780
Where?

356
00:23:45,900 --> 00:23:46,740
You just can't see.

357
00:23:48,420 --> 00:23:49,340
Because you only see

358
00:23:49,940 --> 00:23:51,020
your Doggo.

359
00:23:52,020 --> 00:23:53,020
I'll think about it

360
00:23:54,100 --> 00:23:55,020
for you.

361
00:23:55,620 --> 00:23:57,460
But can we go down for now?

362
00:23:57,700 --> 00:23:58,320
Sure!

363
00:23:59,340 --> 00:24:00,340
- Let's go. - Doggo.

364
00:24:03,340 --> 00:24:04,700
I heard everything.

365
00:24:04,740 --> 00:24:05,740
We are brothers.

366
00:24:05,780 --> 00:24:07,580
You're in need. Take it.

367
00:24:09,700 --> 00:24:10,900
Cutting edge.

368
00:24:12,980 --> 00:24:13,820
What are you doing?

369
00:24:14,060 --> 00:24:15,540
Doggo didn't pay, so he can't read it?

370
00:24:15,980 --> 00:24:17,980
This is customized for personal use.

371
00:24:18,380 --> 00:24:19,900
What do you mean? Make it clear!

372
00:24:20,380 --> 00:24:21,740
This is only for Chen Yuanyuan.

373
00:24:43,620 --> 00:24:44,780
Did someone tell you anything?

374
00:24:47,580 --> 00:24:49,100
I understand. I won't push you.

375
00:24:49,700 --> 00:24:51,300
After all, this is private.

376
00:24:53,300 --> 00:24:54,420
But be nice to Doggo.

377
00:24:55,580 --> 00:24:56,580
Why?

378
00:24:58,260 --> 00:24:59,340
Doggo

379
00:24:59,340 --> 00:25:00,580
is really a dog.

380
00:25:01,420 --> 00:25:02,020
Is that so?

381
00:25:02,580 --> 00:25:04,020
Dogs are naive.

382
00:25:05,180 --> 00:25:06,100
What's happening?

383
00:25:06,860 --> 00:25:07,820
Where's the dog?

384
00:25:13,780 --> 00:25:14,940
Dummy.

385
00:25:15,900 --> 00:25:17,340
- Heard Orange Jasmin? - Yep.

386
00:25:17,340 --> 00:25:17,940
Doggo.

387
00:25:19,580 --> 00:25:20,660
Where to after school?

388
00:25:23,180 --> 00:25:24,340
How about Qin's place?

389
00:25:24,420 --> 00:25:25,020
Sure.

390
00:25:25,500 --> 00:25:26,100
Let's go.

391
00:25:29,180 --> 00:25:30,540
Doggo said nothing!

392
00:25:43,380 --> 00:25:44,060
Faster.

393
00:25:46,300 --> 00:25:46,900
Alright.

394
00:25:50,020 --> 00:25:50,740
Do it, Doggo.

395
00:25:50,940 --> 00:25:51,540
Qin,

396
00:25:51,580 --> 00:25:52,220
let's do it.

397
00:25:52,700 --> 00:25:53,500
Race!

398
00:25:53,940 --> 00:25:54,580
Let's do it!

399
00:26:05,020 --> 00:26:06,500
Son of a turtle, you're so late!

400
00:26:06,820 --> 00:26:08,340
Trying to exhaust me?

401
00:26:08,460 --> 00:26:09,300
My bad.

402
00:26:11,980 --> 00:26:13,300
Son of a turtle.

403
00:26:13,340 --> 00:26:15,500
You're in a good mood today.

404
00:26:16,340 --> 00:26:17,460
You didn't talk back.

405
00:26:17,500 --> 00:26:19,460
It's like my life is lacking motivation.

406
00:26:20,540 --> 00:26:21,380
Is that so?

407
00:26:25,020 --> 00:26:25,940
You got a girlfriend?

408
00:26:28,580 --> 00:26:29,740
It's not like that.

409
00:26:31,340 --> 00:26:33,860
No wonder it seems like you're growing

410
00:26:35,220 --> 00:26:37,300
some manners lately.

411
00:26:40,820 --> 00:26:41,500
Dad?

412
00:26:41,780 --> 00:26:44,020
What counts a girl as your girlfriend?

413
00:26:46,580 --> 00:26:47,980
I've been single for so long.

414
00:26:48,700 --> 00:26:50,580
The only females around me are sows,

415
00:26:50,620 --> 00:26:51,220
and you ask me?

416
00:26:52,940 --> 00:26:54,340
If only mom were here.

417
00:27:10,860 --> 00:27:11,580
For bus tickets.

418
00:27:11,580 --> 00:27:13,100
It's the National Day Holiday.

419
00:27:13,740 --> 00:27:14,940
What bus tickets?

420
00:27:15,180 --> 00:27:16,460
Don't ask me. I don't know.

421
00:27:26,660 --> 00:27:27,660
Thanks, dad!

422
00:27:50,060 --> 00:27:51,740
Excuse me, sir.

423
00:27:52,220 --> 00:27:53,340
Where is this place?

424
00:27:54,160 --> 00:27:54,780
I know this.

425
00:27:55,020 --> 00:27:56,700
I'll drive you. It's a long way from here.

426
00:27:56,860 --> 00:27:57,540
Sir,

427
00:27:57,660 --> 00:27:58,740
how much would it cost?

428
00:27:58,940 --> 00:28:00,340
Close to 200.

429
00:28:00,380 --> 00:28:01,260
Come on, going or not?

430
00:28:02,180 --> 00:28:03,980
Kid, this is the east.

431
00:28:03,980 --> 00:28:05,980
You're going to the western suburbs.

432
00:28:05,980 --> 00:28:06,860
It's really far away.

433
00:28:08,260 --> 00:28:08,880
Come on,

434
00:28:09,580 --> 00:28:10,220
going or not?

435
00:28:10,340 --> 00:28:11,300
Never mind.

436
00:28:12,340 --> 00:28:13,580
Kid, if you're going there...

437
00:28:13,980 --> 00:28:16,260
This is the east, you're headed to the western suburbs.

438
00:28:16,260 --> 00:28:17,020
It's a long way.

439
00:28:17,020 --> 00:28:17,620
Going or not?

440
00:28:33,260 --> 00:28:33,900
Hello.

441
00:28:34,340 --> 00:28:34,940
Mom.

442
00:28:35,140 --> 00:28:36,300
Junjun, it's you.

443
00:28:36,780 --> 00:28:37,580
You're in Chengdu?

444
00:28:37,980 --> 00:28:38,780
Are you alone?

445
00:28:39,100 --> 00:28:41,260
No, I'm here with dad.

446
00:28:41,460 --> 00:28:43,220
I just wanted to stop by to see you.

447
00:28:43,340 --> 00:28:44,380
You're here with your dad.

448
00:28:45,580 --> 00:28:46,380
Junjun,

449
00:28:46,420 --> 00:28:47,860
I have a guest at home.

450
00:28:47,980 --> 00:28:48,580
I'm busy.

451
00:28:49,060 --> 00:28:49,860
It's alright, mom.

452
00:28:50,300 --> 00:28:50,900
Get to it.

453
00:28:51,100 --> 00:28:52,700
After you're done, let's have a meal.

454
00:28:54,040 --> 00:28:55,980
- Alright. - Oh right, mom, I met a girl lately...

455
00:29:11,380 --> 00:29:13,020
Sir, don't serve the dishes yet.

456
00:29:13,060 --> 00:29:14,100
Serve when everyone's here.

457
00:29:14,140 --> 00:29:15,580
Sure, serve when your group comes.

458
00:29:15,660 --> 00:29:16,260
Thanks.

459
00:31:43,260 --> 00:31:45,140
It's too late now. I can't come out.

460
00:31:45,700 --> 00:31:47,260
Has to be tomorrow to hang out.

461
00:31:48,300 --> 00:31:49,580
I was just passing by.

462
00:31:50,100 --> 00:31:51,020
I saw your lights on.

463
00:31:53,300 --> 00:31:54,340
How are you?

464
00:31:56,860 --> 00:31:58,780
I went to Chengdu to see my mom today.

465
00:32:00,260 --> 00:32:00,900
Did you see her?

466
00:32:07,680 --> 00:32:08,300
You didn't.

467
00:32:08,300 --> 00:32:09,580
She has a new family.

468
00:32:11,900 --> 00:32:12,940
She's happy.

469
00:32:18,540 --> 00:32:19,820
It's alright. Go to bed.

470
00:32:20,500 --> 00:32:21,820
It's fine. Let's talk for a while.

471
00:32:22,660 --> 00:32:23,460
Haven't had dinner.

472
00:32:23,500 --> 00:32:24,180
I'll grab a meal.

473
00:32:36,980 --> 00:32:37,980
Try these.

474
00:32:40,380 --> 00:32:40,980
How is it?

475
00:32:43,420 --> 00:32:44,040
Delicious.

476
00:32:50,900 --> 00:32:52,020
Now try these.

477
00:33:47,060 --> 00:33:47,940
That's all I have.

478
00:33:49,460 --> 00:33:50,060
Delicious.

479
00:33:51,620 --> 00:33:52,860
They won't fill your stomach,

480
00:33:53,140 --> 00:33:54,460
but you must lift your spirits.

481
00:33:55,740 --> 00:33:56,660
Then good night.

482
00:33:57,100 --> 00:33:57,900
I'm leaving.

483
00:33:58,580 --> 00:33:59,380
Good night.

484
00:33:59,940 --> 00:34:00,740
Good night.

485
00:34:46,020 --> 00:34:47,100
Jiaojiao,

486
00:34:47,300 --> 00:34:49,299
why don't you go say hi to your classmate?

487
00:34:51,140 --> 00:34:52,980
Why hasn't Doggo come back yet?

488
00:34:55,739 --> 00:34:56,860
Why should I talk to him?

489
00:34:58,460 --> 00:34:59,339
That's impolite.

490
00:34:59,580 --> 00:35:00,180
Take it.

491
00:35:16,540 --> 00:35:18,140
Stop it!

492
00:35:19,380 --> 00:35:20,739
Where did your Anran take Doggo

493
00:35:20,739 --> 00:35:21,660
this time?

494
00:35:22,060 --> 00:35:23,259
He's still not back so late.

495
00:35:25,220 --> 00:35:26,660
I've sat here for so long,

496
00:35:26,819 --> 00:35:28,060
and you didn't even look at me.

497
00:35:29,180 --> 00:35:30,500
All you have in mind is Doggo.

498
00:35:30,980 --> 00:35:33,060
Am I that different from Doggo?

499
00:35:34,060 --> 00:35:35,140
Of course.

500
00:35:35,140 --> 00:35:35,900
What is it?

501
00:35:37,220 --> 00:35:38,700
You're taller and more handsome.

502
00:35:42,780 --> 00:35:44,580
You've always thought so?

503
00:35:45,340 --> 00:35:47,500
Everyone in the country can tell that.

504
00:35:50,860 --> 00:35:51,700
I think so too.

505
00:35:53,340 --> 00:35:54,140
Oh my.

506
00:36:05,700 --> 00:36:07,180
Aunty, two noodles.

507
00:36:07,380 --> 00:36:08,700
Sure, take a seat.

508
00:36:10,020 --> 00:36:10,740
Bye, Aunty.

509
00:36:12,660 --> 00:36:14,180
Jiaojiao, your classmate is leaving.

510
00:36:14,180 --> 00:36:15,180
Go see him off.

511
00:36:16,460 --> 00:36:17,540
Alright, I'll walk you.

512
00:36:25,100 --> 00:36:26,660
Why do you only like Doggo?

513
00:36:27,740 --> 00:36:29,620
I've played with them since I was a kid.

514
00:36:29,660 --> 00:36:30,980
I don't know who else to like.

515
00:36:32,620 --> 00:36:33,980
Do you know what it means to like?

516
00:36:34,820 --> 00:36:35,420
You do?

517
00:36:36,300 --> 00:36:37,100
A little.

518
00:36:38,100 --> 00:36:39,260
For example,

519
00:36:39,300 --> 00:36:42,060
one time, I saw a very special girl,

520
00:36:42,980 --> 00:36:44,140
and I liked her.

521
00:36:44,340 --> 00:36:45,340
When was that?

522
00:36:47,060 --> 00:36:47,740
Can't remember.

523
00:36:50,980 --> 00:36:52,900
Go home now. It's so late.

524
00:36:55,340 --> 00:36:56,340
Ask again.

525
00:36:56,620 --> 00:36:57,340
Ask again,

526
00:36:57,580 --> 00:36:58,980
and maybe I'll tell you.

527
00:37:00,220 --> 00:37:02,780
It's not like you don't know. I have a big mouth.

528
00:37:03,260 --> 00:37:04,700
Forget it, I'll tell everyone.

529
00:37:05,340 --> 00:37:06,140
Bye.

530
00:37:32,140 --> 00:37:32,860
I'm leaving.

531
00:37:41,220 --> 00:37:41,980
What a coincidence.

532
00:37:45,540 --> 00:37:46,540
What are you doing here?

533
00:37:47,180 --> 00:37:48,860
I'm wandering after school.

534
00:37:48,940 --> 00:37:50,660
I didn't expect to see you here.

535
00:37:51,260 --> 00:37:52,420
Aren't you taking the exam?

536
00:37:52,740 --> 00:37:53,740
Stop wandering.

537
00:37:54,140 --> 00:37:55,340
I want to go home,

538
00:37:56,260 --> 00:37:57,420
but I don't know the way.

539
00:37:58,060 --> 00:37:59,300
Go where you came from.

540
00:37:59,860 --> 00:38:00,580
I don't remember.

541
00:38:01,820 --> 00:38:02,440
Where's Doggo?

542
00:38:02,980 --> 00:38:03,980
He's not with me today.

543
00:38:04,340 --> 00:38:05,820
How about you take me for a walk.

544
00:38:05,820 --> 00:38:07,580
I'll probably pick up the way to go home.

545
00:38:12,860 --> 00:38:13,740
Troublesome.

546
00:38:14,660 --> 00:38:15,300
Let's go.

547
00:38:18,700 --> 00:38:19,340
Qin,

548
00:38:19,860 --> 00:38:20,620
are you hungry?

549
00:38:20,620 --> 00:38:21,820
Maybe we can grab a meal,

550
00:38:21,820 --> 00:38:22,860
if you're not busy?

551
00:38:22,860 --> 00:38:23,700
I am.

552
00:38:23,700 --> 00:38:24,340
I mean,

553
00:38:24,380 --> 00:38:27,140
I know a place that makes good noodles.

554
00:38:32,380 --> 00:38:33,260
You're really annoying

555
00:38:33,340 --> 00:38:34,780
Can you stop making me see you?

556
00:38:34,820 --> 00:38:36,420
You like to play pool or this place?

557
00:38:36,420 --> 00:38:37,500
How did you end up here?

558
00:38:38,660 --> 00:38:40,300
You're not busy, but I am.

559
00:38:43,620 --> 00:38:45,140
I just want to have some noodles.

560
00:38:45,860 --> 00:38:46,700
Go do your business.

561
00:38:47,100 --> 00:38:47,900
I'll leave.

562
00:38:48,780 --> 00:38:50,220
Will you go home after some noodles?

563
00:38:52,740 --> 00:38:53,380
Yes.

564
00:38:59,180 --> 00:39:00,660
Do you really think I'm annoying?

565
00:39:00,940 --> 00:39:01,540
No.

566
00:39:01,540 --> 00:39:02,940
Then why did you yell at me?

567
00:39:04,100 --> 00:39:05,460
Are we having noodles or not?

568
00:39:09,940 --> 00:39:11,060
Are we?

569
00:39:12,580 --> 00:39:13,220
Yes.

570
00:39:15,220 --> 00:39:16,100
This is my home.

571
00:39:22,860 --> 00:39:24,460
Can I have noodles with you again?

572
00:39:27,100 --> 00:39:28,180
We'll see.

573
00:39:28,900 --> 00:39:29,740
Bye.

574
00:39:29,740 --> 00:39:30,620
See you next time.

575
00:39:38,660 --> 00:39:39,940
Why are you here?

576
00:39:39,980 --> 00:39:40,940
Why is he here?

577
00:39:41,540 --> 00:39:42,460
We ran into each other.

578
00:39:44,300 --> 00:39:45,860
Are you still mad at him?

579
00:39:46,300 --> 00:39:47,500
I'm mad at you.

580
00:39:47,740 --> 00:39:48,460
Why?

581
00:39:49,380 --> 00:39:50,100
Always felt...

582
00:39:50,140 --> 00:39:50,980
Felt what?

583
00:39:53,180 --> 00:39:53,940
Nothing

584
00:39:54,620 --> 00:39:56,900
We're friends. As long as you're happy,

585
00:39:57,300 --> 00:39:58,740
what can I do?

586
00:39:58,860 --> 00:40:00,420
You don't seem that willing.

587
00:40:04,020 --> 00:40:04,820
Oh right.

588
00:40:04,860 --> 00:40:07,100
We should apply to universities overseas next month.

589
00:40:08,820 --> 00:40:09,780
Be honest,

590
00:40:10,300 --> 00:40:11,620
do you really want to go abroad?

591
00:40:12,700 --> 00:40:13,320
You?

592
00:40:14,820 --> 00:40:15,740
I haven't decided yet.

593
00:40:17,580 --> 00:40:18,180
Me neither.

594
00:40:21,220 --> 00:40:22,580
I'm having second thoughts.

595
00:40:23,300 --> 00:40:24,780
I finally found him.

596
00:40:25,740 --> 00:40:27,060
I don't want to go abroad anymore.

597
00:40:27,060 --> 00:40:27,820
Just for him?

598
00:40:29,220 --> 00:40:30,740
Yes. For him.

599
00:40:35,420 --> 00:40:36,040
Tiantian

600
00:40:36,540 --> 00:40:38,740
You'll apply to school abroad next month, right?

601
00:40:41,260 --> 00:40:42,740
Anran will go with you.

602
00:40:42,780 --> 00:40:44,340
Seems like all files needed are ready.

603
00:40:47,500 --> 00:40:49,820
You never needed me to take care of you.

604
00:40:49,820 --> 00:40:52,180
But this thing is more important than anything else.

605
00:40:52,740 --> 00:40:53,780
You know that, right?

606
00:40:54,140 --> 00:40:55,020
Don't miss the window.

607
00:40:56,660 --> 00:40:57,580
Understand?

608
00:41:00,940 --> 00:41:01,560
Tiantian.

609
00:41:02,020 --> 00:41:03,780
I happened to pass by your school

610
00:41:03,780 --> 00:41:05,060
I wanted to pick you up.

611
00:41:07,340 --> 00:41:08,580
When?

612
00:41:08,620 --> 00:41:09,580
Why didn't I see you?

613
00:41:10,140 --> 00:41:10,980
But I saw you

614
00:41:10,980 --> 00:41:12,220
walking with another girl,

615
00:41:12,820 --> 00:41:13,500
so

616
00:41:13,860 --> 00:41:15,100
I didn't call you.

617
00:41:18,980 --> 00:41:20,820
That's my desk-mate.

618
00:41:20,860 --> 00:41:23,540
The guy with her left early that day.

619
00:41:23,540 --> 00:41:25,500
So I walked along with her for a while.

620
00:41:32,580 --> 00:41:33,180
What?

621
00:41:33,900 --> 00:41:34,940
Expensive shoes, so what?

622
00:41:35,740 --> 00:41:36,860
Such a child.

623
00:41:54,940 --> 00:41:55,620
Come here.

624
00:41:56,140 --> 00:41:56,780
All of you!

625
00:41:57,380 --> 00:41:58,940
Do you know anything about a marathon?

626
00:41:59,580 --> 00:42:01,060
If you keep sprinting the first half,

627
00:42:01,460 --> 00:42:03,180
then you'll walk for the second half.

628
00:42:04,420 --> 00:42:06,540
You must run with the fastest average speed.

629
00:42:06,740 --> 00:42:07,380
Understand?

630
00:42:08,740 --> 00:42:09,660
Brainless.

631
00:42:09,900 --> 00:42:11,300
None of your business if I die.

632
00:42:11,300 --> 00:42:12,100
Just mind your own.

633
00:42:12,100 --> 00:42:13,180
Self-centered.

634
00:42:14,940 --> 00:42:15,860
You have a temper.

635
00:42:18,220 --> 00:42:19,300
You're the team lead!

636
00:42:20,620 --> 00:42:22,180
You're not responsible for the team?

637
00:42:23,740 --> 00:42:24,340
Take it.

638
00:42:25,300 --> 00:42:26,420
Keep everyone training.

639
00:42:26,420 --> 00:42:28,100
I have things to do. You're on your own.

640
00:42:38,820 --> 00:42:39,420
Here.

641
00:42:40,020 --> 00:42:40,660
Team lead,

642
00:42:42,140 --> 00:42:43,820
we can't practice like this today, right?

643
00:42:44,620 --> 00:42:45,900
My mom needs me at home.

644
00:42:46,500 --> 00:42:47,100
See you.

645
00:42:48,980 --> 00:42:51,300
I'm starving. Should we go eat something?

646
00:42:51,620 --> 00:42:52,300
Sure,

647
00:42:52,300 --> 00:42:53,300
let's go to Qin's place.

648
00:42:55,380 --> 00:42:56,420
Can I also come?

649
00:42:59,300 --> 00:42:59,920
Sure.

650
00:43:00,860 --> 00:43:02,020
Ma Tian should come along.

651
00:43:02,480 --> 00:43:03,100
Hey.

652
00:43:03,100 --> 00:43:04,020
Which side are you on?

653
00:43:04,180 --> 00:43:05,580
Helping you build team chemistry.

654
00:43:08,220 --> 00:43:09,180
Then,

655
00:43:09,300 --> 00:43:10,140
Ma Tian should pay!

656
00:43:10,500 --> 00:43:11,860
Yeah, we're going to run together.

657
00:43:12,060 --> 00:43:12,700
Let's go.

658
00:43:12,700 --> 00:43:13,660
Everyone goes.

659
00:43:13,940 --> 00:43:15,260
Skewers and training together.

660
00:43:15,940 --> 00:43:16,540
Go.

661
00:43:17,540 --> 00:43:19,300
Haven't had skewers for so long!

662
00:43:19,300 --> 00:43:20,660
Let's go.

663
00:43:22,460 --> 00:43:23,220
Off we go.

664
00:43:27,540 --> 00:43:28,260
Why do you think

665
00:43:28,260 --> 00:43:29,780
Qin suddenly went to sell skewers?

666
00:43:30,100 --> 00:43:30,700
No idea.

667
00:43:30,940 --> 00:43:32,700
Not coming to school to sell skewers.

668
00:43:34,100 --> 00:43:35,140
Family business.

669
00:43:35,500 --> 00:43:36,380
Don't mention it.

670
00:43:38,380 --> 00:43:39,000
Hurry up.

671
00:43:42,620 --> 00:43:44,460
Doing business without paying for protection.

672
00:43:45,500 --> 00:43:46,380
Beat him.

673
00:43:46,460 --> 00:43:47,540
Pay for protection!

674
00:43:48,540 --> 00:43:49,160
Qin

675
00:43:52,380 --> 00:43:52,980
Danger!

676
00:44:01,580 --> 00:44:02,500
Why did you come here?

677
00:44:02,500 --> 00:44:03,900
Or we wouldn't know you're alone.

678
00:44:04,220 --> 00:44:04,900
We'll help you.

679
00:44:05,540 --> 00:44:06,940
Beat him to death!

680
00:44:08,700 --> 00:44:09,820
Doggo, run!

681
00:44:10,660 --> 00:44:11,460
Teaty, run!

682
00:44:14,900 --> 00:44:15,540
Qin

683
00:44:23,620 --> 00:44:24,240
Anran

684
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:28,300
Anran, why did you come?

685
00:44:31,460 --> 00:44:32,300
Liu Wenqin!

686
00:44:33,380 --> 00:44:34,260
Run!

687
00:44:38,820 --> 00:44:40,020
What are you doing here?

688
00:45:27,780 --> 00:45:29,140
Doggo, run!

689
00:45:42,460 --> 00:45:43,820
They're all gone now.

690
00:45:44,180 --> 00:45:45,540
You're my target today.

691
00:46:00,180 --> 00:46:00,940
Where's Doggo?

692
00:46:01,060 --> 00:46:02,260
Don't worry about Doggo.

693
00:46:02,460 --> 00:46:03,620
No one outruns him.

694
00:46:06,500 --> 00:46:08,020
Jiaojiao!

695
00:46:09,220 --> 00:46:09,900
Try running now!

696
00:46:11,100 --> 00:46:11,800
That girl

697
00:46:11,800 --> 00:46:12,380
Run now!

698
00:46:12,380 --> 00:46:13,580
picked up Liu Wenqin and ran!

699
00:46:13,900 --> 00:46:14,740
Didn't look at you.

700
00:46:16,140 --> 00:46:17,340
You dummy.

701
00:46:17,420 --> 00:46:18,140
Dummy.

702
00:46:19,300 --> 00:46:20,780
Get up!

703
00:46:20,780 --> 00:46:21,380
Get up.

704
00:46:25,820 --> 00:46:26,500
Run!

705
00:46:29,100 --> 00:46:29,720
Stop!

706
00:46:30,380 --> 00:46:31,000
Stop!

707
00:46:31,420 --> 00:46:32,220
Stop!

708
00:47:18,780 --> 00:47:20,260
Open up!

709
00:47:21,580 --> 00:47:22,620
Open up now!

710
00:47:30,060 --> 00:47:31,340
Stop looking.

711
00:47:31,340 --> 00:47:32,940
There's only one exit.

712
00:47:35,020 --> 00:47:36,220
There's not even a back door.

713
00:47:37,580 --> 00:47:39,180
This is the lower half of the city.

714
00:47:41,460 --> 00:47:43,060
How dare they ask for a protection fee.

715
00:47:43,060 --> 00:47:44,380
They're messing with us.

716
00:47:44,380 --> 00:47:45,620
We can't let them slip.

717
00:47:45,620 --> 00:47:46,900
These punks must pay back!

718
00:47:47,740 --> 00:47:48,820
Why are you following me?

719
00:47:50,580 --> 00:47:52,300
Did you become like this because of me?

720
00:47:52,460 --> 00:47:54,260
This is my choice. Nothing to do with you.

721
00:47:54,540 --> 00:47:55,420
I think this is great!

722
00:47:55,420 --> 00:47:56,420
What's great?

723
00:47:56,420 --> 00:47:57,740
Free and living the life!

724
00:47:58,900 --> 00:48:00,460
But you're only 18 years old!

725
00:48:05,420 --> 00:48:07,140
When has life allowed me to be 18 years old!

726
00:48:11,340 --> 00:48:12,140
Take me.

727
00:48:21,060 --> 00:48:22,140
Stop following me.

728
00:48:24,980 --> 00:48:25,580
Get lost!

729
00:48:32,820 --> 00:48:33,940
Thank you for just now.

730
00:48:38,260 --> 00:48:39,060
Were you scared?

731
00:48:42,100 --> 00:48:43,100
What do you think?

732
00:48:43,180 --> 00:48:44,420
Who knows what those people

733
00:48:44,420 --> 00:48:45,700
outside are holding.

734
00:48:53,060 --> 00:48:54,020
If we can get out

735
00:48:54,020 --> 00:48:55,380
safe today,

736
00:48:55,900 --> 00:48:57,780
then let's go get a marathon champion together,

737
00:48:58,060 --> 00:48:59,020
and honor our school.

738
00:49:00,740 --> 00:49:02,580
Is this the time to think about that?

739
00:49:02,660 --> 00:49:03,940
Or what else can I talk to you?

740
00:49:15,500 --> 00:49:17,660
Sure. Honor our school!

741
00:49:17,740 --> 00:49:19,220
Honor our school!

742
00:49:19,220 --> 00:49:20,820
If I go out,

743
00:49:20,860 --> 00:49:22,900
I'll study hard

744
00:49:23,060 --> 00:49:24,300
Strive every day!

745
00:49:24,420 --> 00:49:25,660
Strive every day!

746
00:49:25,940 --> 00:49:27,460
Study rigorously!

747
00:49:27,460 --> 00:49:28,860
Study rigorously!

748
00:49:28,860 --> 00:49:30,300
Climb to the top!

749
00:49:30,300 --> 00:49:31,580
Climb to the top!

750
00:49:31,580 --> 00:49:32,780
Unity and innovation!

751
00:49:32,780 --> 00:49:34,300
Unity and innovation!

752
00:49:34,300 --> 00:49:36,380
Forge a better future!

753
00:49:36,380 --> 00:49:37,180
Forge a better...

754
00:49:51,380 --> 00:49:52,300
You alright?

755
00:49:53,260 --> 00:49:53,980
Fine.

756
00:49:54,860 --> 00:49:55,700
Buried in the past.

757
00:50:02,580 --> 00:50:03,220
What's that?

758
00:50:06,740 --> 00:50:07,340
Me and her.

759
00:50:17,820 --> 00:50:18,900
None of my business.
